The leaders of India, Brazil, South Africa, and the United States met during the G20 Leaders' Summit in New Delhi to reaffirm their commitment to the G20 as the leading forum for international economic cooperation. They aim to address global challenges and build on the progress made during India's G20 Presidency. The leaders also welcomed the G20's commitment to strengthen multilateral development banks, highlighting the potential for collaboration through the G20 to support their respective populations towards a better future.